Thousands of city residents flocked the Uhuru Stadium to celebrate the Easter, with prayers for the nation taking the centre stage. The country s constitution provides for freedom of worship as long as one doesn t infringe on the rights of others...we will not tolerate anybody wielding a machete and forcing others to follow what he or she believes in, Mr Mwigulu said amid ovation from the crowd.He argued that Tanzania will always be a nation of different religions, commending the religious leaders and their believers for their critical role in praying for the nation s peace.Chairman of the Pentecostal Churches in Dar es Salaam Reverend Bruno Mwakibola pointed out that it is grateful that the country has God-fearing President John Magufuli who always keeps God after him at everything.